records.addlTxt:
10:40 AM Defendant Alena M Mendez in court.  Attorney Priya Barnes in court for Alena M Mendez.  Prosecuting attorney Alyssa M. Schaller in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
State files an amended information.  Victim rights have been complied with by the Waukesha County District Attorneys Office. 
Defendant enters a plea of no contest to Count 1,  Court finds defendant guilty. 
The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

45 DAYS HUBER, w/Standard Release Conditions (CREDIT - 2 days);

TERM OF PROBATION:  1 YEAR;

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION: 
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*Follow through with any assessments, evaluations, treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent; 
*No violent contact with victim; 
*DNA sample to be provided;
*No presence on any premises whose primary business is serving or selling alcohol (i.e bars, taverns, or liquor stores).

COURT COSTS:  $243 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

Upon Petition - Court will consider early termination of probation at any point after 7 months, if all conditions are met and agent deems appropriate.
